OL,3,CHow to host the Irish Open
OL,5,FEammon says the nature of the sand at
OL,6,Fthe course means it can often be blown
OL,7,Fout of the bunkers meaning the green
OL,8,Fstaff are constantly re-filling them:
OL,9,F"These last few days we have maybe put
OL,10,Fin 60-70 tonnes of sand in the
OL,11,Fbunkers."
OL,13,FDespite its timeless nature, the
OL,14,Fcourse has been subtly tweaked since
OL,15,Fthe Irish Open was last held here in
OL,16,F2015.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/7
