OL,3,CHow to host the Irish Open
OL,5,FOnce the course is ready to go for the
OL,6,Ffour days of competition it is over to
OL,7,Fthe 100s of volunteers from golf clubs
OL,8,Facross the island then step in to make
OL,9,Fsure the tournament runs well.
OL,11,F"I think the number is up somewhere
OL,12,Faround 700 that we need to do the
OL,13,Fjob," Kevan says.
OL,15,F"It is a very well organised thing
OL,16,Fwhere they will have various jobs at
OL,17,Fcrossover points, on to grandstands,
OL,18,Flooking after tee boxes, look after
OL,19,Fgreens, holding up the quiet please
OL,20,Fsigns that type of thing.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/7
